re's a practical tension to navigate:\n\nThe current bubble menu has **non-trivial positioning logic** (it uses TipTap's `BubbleMenu` from `@tiptap/react/menus` which handles show/hide based on selection, positioning via Tippy.js, and `shouldShow` callbacks). The `BubbleMenu.Root` needs to encapsulate all of that so users don't have to wire it up themselves.\n\nSo the compound component tree would really be:\n\n```tsx\n// BubbleMenu.Root handles: TipTap BubbleMenu positioning, shouldShow logic,\n// state management for which sub-menus are open\n<BubbleMenu.Root>\n  {/* These just render buttons and dispatch commands */}\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector>\n    <MyVariablesButton />  {/* plugin slot */}\n  </BubbleMenu.LinkSelector>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\nThis maps cleanly because `Root` owns the hard part (positioning + visibility), and children are just UI buttons that call `editor.chain().focus().toggleBold().run()`.",
