          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "## Final Design: Compound Component Primitives for Bubble Menu\n\n### Package: `@react-email/editor`\n\nEverything lives in the existing editor package under a new `ui/` directory alongside the existing `core/`, `extensions/`, `plugins/`, and `utils/` directories.\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\npackages/editor/src/\n  index.ts                          # existing - add ui re-exports\n  ui/\n    index.ts                        # barrel: export * from './bubble-menu'\n    bubble-menu/\n      index.ts                      # barrel for all compound components\n      context.tsx                   # BubbleMenuContext (shared state between components)\n      root.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Root - wraps TipTap BubbleMenu, provides context\n      group.tsx                     # BubbleMenu.Group - visual grouping container\n      separator.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Separator - divider between groups\n      item.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Item - generic toggle button primitive\n      bold.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Bold - pre-wired bold toggle\n      italic.tsx                    # BubbleMenu.Italic\n      underline.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Underline\n      strike.tsx                    # BubbleMenu.Strike\n      code.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Code\n      uppercase.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Uppercase\n      align-left.tsx                # BubbleMenu.AlignLeft\n      align-center.tsx              # BubbleMenu.AlignCenter\n      align-right.tsx               # BubbleMenu.AlignRight\n      node-selector.tsx             # BubbleMenu.NodeSelector - block type dropdown\n      link-selector.tsx             # BubbleMenu.LinkSelector - link input with plugin slot\n```\n\n### Component API Design\n\n**`BubbleMenu.Root`** - The positioning/visibility wrapper.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuRootProps {\n  /** Nodes that should NOT trigger the bubble menu */\n  excludeNodes?: string[];\n  /** TipTap BubbleMenu placement */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from selection in px */\n  offset?: number;\n  /** Additional className on the outer wrapper */\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nInternally wraps TipTap's `BubbleMenu` from `@tiptap/react/menus`. Uses `useCurrentEditor()` to get the editor instance. Provides a `BubbleMenuContext` to children with:\n- `editor` instance\n- `onHide` callback (to reset open states)\n\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu`\n\n---\n\n**`BubbleMenu.Group`** - Groups items visually.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuGroupProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nJust a `<div>` wrapper. Data attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-group`.\n\n---\n\n**`BubbleMenu.Separator`** - Divider between groups.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuSeparatorProps {\n  className?: string;\n}\n```\n\nRenders a `<div role=\"separator\">`. Data attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-separator`.\n\n---\n\n**`BubbleMenu.Item`** - Generic toggle button primitive.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuItemProps {\n  /** Used for aria-label and data-item attribute */\n  name: string;\n  /** Whether this item is currently active */\n  isActive: boolean;\n  /** Called when clicked */\n  onCommand: () => void;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders a `<button>` with `aria-label`, `aria-pressed`. Data attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-item`, `data-active` when active.\n\n---\n\n**Pre-wired items** (`BubbleMenu.Bold`, `BubbleMenu.Italic`, etc.) - Zero-config items.\n\n```tsx\ninterface PreWiredItemProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Override the default icon */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nEach reads the editor from context, wires up `isActive` and `command` automatically. If no `children`, renders a default icon from `lucide-react`. Data attributes: inherit from `Item` + `data-item=\"bold\"` etc.\n\n**Important**: `lucide-react` becomes a peer dependency (already used in the dashboard).\n\n---\n\n**`BubbleMenu.NodeSelector`** - Block type dropdown.\n\n```tsx\ninterface NodeSelectorProps {\n  /** Items to exclude from the dropdown */\n  omit?: string[];\n  className?: string;\n  /** Override the trigger content */\n  triggerContent?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nUses `@radix-ui/react-popover` (peer dep) internally. Shows the active block type name in the trigger. Data attributes: `data-re-node-selector`, `data-open` when expanded.\n\n---\n\n**`BubbleMenu.LinkSelector`** - Link input with plugin slot.\n\n```tsx\ninterface LinkSelectorProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Whether to show the link icon toggle button */\n  showToggle?: boolean;\n  /** Custom URL validator (default: basic URL validation) */\n  validateUrl?: (value: string) => string | null;\n  /** Called when link is applied */\n  onLinkApply?: (href: string) => void;\n  /** Called when link is removed */\n  onLinkRemove?: () => void;\n  /** Plugin slot: extra actions rendered inside the link input form */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nThe `children` slot is how Resend injects `<VariablesDropdown>`. Data attributes: `data-re-link-selector`, `data-has-link` when a link exists.\n\nThe link input handles:\n- Escape to cancel (cleans up phantom `#` links)\n- Click-outside to submit\n- Submit on Enter\n- Unlink button when link exists\n\nBut does NOT include:\n- `VARIABLE_PATTERN` validation (Resend-specific)\n- `showToast` (Resend-specific)\n- `EDITOR_CONTENT_ID` (Resend-specific)\n\nInstead, `validateUrl` lets users plug in their own validation, and `onLinkApply`/`onLinkRemove` are callbacks for side effects.\n\n---\n\n### Usage Examples\n\n**Minimal (all defaults):**\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\n\n<BubbleMenu.Root>\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n    <BubbleMenu.Underline />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n**Resend's consumption (in dashboard):**\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\nimport { VariablesDropdown } from '../plugins/variables/dropdown';\nimport { cn } from '@/lib/cn';\n\n<BubbleMenu.Root\n  excludeNodes={['image', 'button', 'htmlContent', 'socialLinks', 'youtube', 'twitter']}\n  className=\"bg-background rounded-xl border border-gray-3 shadow-xl\"\n>\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector className=\"...\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector\n    validateUrl={(value) => {\n      if (VARIABLE_PATTERN.test(value)) return value;\n      return getUrlFromString(value);\n    }}\n    onLinkApply={() => {}}\n    onLinkRemove={() => {\n      showToast({ title: '...' });\n    }}\n  >\n    <VariablesDropdown onVariableSelect={handleVariableSelect} modal>\n      <button className=\"...\">\n        <IconVariable className=\"size-4\" />\n      </button>\n    </VariablesDropdown>\n  </BubbleMenu.LinkSelector>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Underline className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Strike className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Code className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Uppercase className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignLeft className=\"...\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignCenter className=\"...\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignRight className=\"...\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n**Custom item (user extending):**\n```tsx\n<BubbleMenu.Group>\n  <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n  <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n  <BubbleMenu.Item\n    name=\"highlight\"\n    isActive={editor.isActive('highlight')}\n    onCommand={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleHighlight().run()}\n  >\n    <HighlightIcon className=\"h-4 w-4\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Item>\n</BubbleMenu.Group>\n```\n\n---\n\n### New Dependencies for `@react-email/editor`\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|-----------|------|--------|\n| `@radix-ui/react-popover` | peer | NodeSelector dropdown |\n| `lucide-react` | peer | Default icons for pre-wired items |\n\nBoth are already used in the dashboard so there's no new weight for Resend. For external users, peer deps make them opt-in.\n\n---\n\n### What Gets Removed from Dashboard\n\nAfter extracting, the dashboard's `ui/bubble-menu/` directory imports from `@react-email/editor` instead. The current 6 files collapse into a single composition file that applies Resend's styles and injects the `VariablesDropdown`.\n\n---\n\n### Unresolved Questions\n\n1. Should `lucide-react` be a peer dep, or should we accept icon components via props/children and have no default icons? (tradeoff: simpler API vs smaller dep surface)\n2. The `editorEventBus.on('add-link')` listener in the current bubble menu programmatically opens the link selector. Should `BubbleMenu.Root` expose an imperative API for this, or should we use the event bus pattern in the open-source version too?\n3. The `NodeSelector` currently uses Resend's `dropdown` shared styles from `@/ui/shared`. The open-source version would render unstyled Radix Popover content - do we want to ship a minimal CSS file for functional layout (flex, gap) or leave that entirely to users?\n\n---\n\nDoes this design look right? Any sections you want me to revise before we write the design doc and move to implementation planning?",
