            "content": "# Bubble Menu Compound Components Design\n\n## Context\n\nThe Resend dashboard editor V2 (`dashboard/src/components/editor-v2/`) has a bubble menu system that appears on text selection. We're extracting the text formatting bubble menu into `@react-email/editor` as an open-source compound component primitive, following a Radix UI-inspired architecture.\n\nThe goal: provide unstyled, composable building blocks that give developers full control over their bubble menu UI while encapsulating the complex TipTap positioning/visibility logic.\n\n### Layering model\n\n```\nLayer 0: Primitives (unstyled, composable, data-attributes) <-- this design\n   |\nLayer 1: Default compositions (pre-assembled, optional import) <-- future\n   |\nLayer 2: Themed/styled versions (CSS themes) <-- future\n```\n\nLayer 0 is the foundation. Nothing prevents shipping layers 1 and 2 later as compositions of the same primitives.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Text formatting bubble menu only (not link/image/button bubble menus)\n- Primitives only (no pre-composed defaults yet)\n- Ships in existing `@react-email/editor` package\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Approach: Compound components (Radix UI-inspired)\n\nEach sub-component is a standalone primitive. `BubbleMenu.Root` handles the hard parts (TipTap positioning, selection detection, visibility logic). Children are simple UI buttons that dispatch editor commands.\n\nRejected alternatives:\n- **Headless hook + default component (Base UI-style)**: `slotProps` becomes unnecessary when compound components let you compose directly. The composition IS the API.\n- **Configurable component + recipes (shadcn/ui-style)**: Tailwind dependency for defaults, copy-paste recipes diverge from source, less composable for structural changes.\n\n### File structure\n\n```\npackages/editor/src/\n  index.ts                          # add ui re-exports\n  ui/\n    index.ts                        # barrel: export * from './bubble-menu'\n    bubble-menu/\n      index.ts                      # barrel for all compound components\n      bubble-menu.css               # minimal functional CSS (layout/positioning only)\n      context.tsx                   # BubbleMenuContext (shared state)\n      root.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Root\n      group.tsx                     # BubbleMenu.Group\n      separator.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Separator\n      item.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Item (generic toggle)\n      bold.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Bold (pre-wired)\n      italic.tsx                    # BubbleMenu.Italic\n      underline.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Underline\n      strike.tsx                    # BubbleMenu.Strike\n      code.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Code\n      uppercase.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Uppercase\n      align-left.tsx                # BubbleMenu.AlignLeft\n      align-center.tsx              # BubbleMenu.AlignCenter\n      align-right.tsx               # BubbleMenu.AlignRight\n      node-selector.tsx             # BubbleMenu.NodeSelector\n      link-selector.tsx             # BubbleMenu.LinkSelector\n```\n\n### New dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|-----------|------|--------|\n| `@radix-ui/react-popover` | peer | NodeSelector dropdown |\n| `lucide-react` | peer | Default icons for pre-wired items |\n\nBoth already used in the dashboard - zero new weight for Resend.\n\n## Component API\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Root`\n\nWraps TipTap's `BubbleMenu` from `@tiptap/react/menus`. Provides context to children. Handles show/hide logic and event bus integration.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuRootProps {\n  /** Nodes that should NOT trigger the bubble menu */\n  excludeNodes?: string[];\n  /** TipTap BubbleMenu placement */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from selection in px */\n  offset?: number;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nInternal responsibilities:\n- Wraps `<BubbleMenu>` from `@tiptap/react/menus`\n- Reads editor via `useCurrentEditor()`\n- Provides `BubbleMenuContext` with: `editor`, `onHide` callback\n- Listens to `editorEventBus.on('add-link')` to programmatically open link selector\n- Default `shouldShow`: returns `false` for nodes in `excludeNodes`, returns `true` when selection content size > 0\n\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Group`\n\nVisual grouping container for related items.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuGroupProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: `<div role=\"group\">`\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-group`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Separator`\n\nDivider between groups.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuSeparatorProps {\n  className?: string;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: `<div role=\"separator\">`\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-separator`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Item`\n\nGeneric toggle button primitive. Used directly for custom items, or internally by pre-wired items.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuItemProps {\n  /** Used for aria-label and data attribute */\n  name: string;\n  /** Whether this item is currently active */\n  isActive: boolean;\n  /** Called when clicked */\n  onCommand: () => void;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: `<button type=\"button\" aria-label={name} aria-pressed={isActive}>`\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-item`, `data-item={name}`, `data-active` when pressed\n\n### Pre-wired items\n\n`BubbleMenu.Bold`, `Italic`, `Underline`, `Strike`, `Code`, `Uppercase`, `AlignLeft`, `AlignCenter`, `AlignRight`\n\n```tsx\ninterface PreWiredItemProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Override the default icon */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nEach reads editor from context, auto-wires `isActive` and `command`. Renders default lucide icon if no children. Internally delegates to `BubbleMenu.Item`.\n\nData attributes: inherit from `Item` + `data-item=\"bold\"` (etc.)\n\n### `BubbleMenu.NodeSelector`\n\nBlock type dropdown (Text, Title, Subtitle, Heading, Bullet List, Numbered List, Quote, Code). Uses `@radix-ui/react-popover`.\n\n```tsx\ninterface NodeSelectorProps {\n  /** Block types to exclude */\n  omit?: string[];\n  className?: string;\n  /** Override the trigger content (default: active item name + chevron) */\n  triggerContent?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: Radix `Popover.Root` > `Popover.Trigger` + `Popover.Content` with list of block type buttons.\nData attributes: `data-re-node-selector`, `data-open` when expanded, items get `data-re-node-selector-item` + `data-active`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.LinkSelector`\n\nLink input form with plugin slot for custom actions (e.g., variable insertion).\n\n```tsx\ninterface LinkSelectorProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Whether to show the link icon toggle button (default: true) */\n  showToggle?: boolean;\n  /** Custom URL validator. Return the valid URL or null. Default: basic URL validation */\n  validateUrl?: (value: string) => string | null;\n  /** Called after link is applied */\n  onLinkApply?: (href: string) => void;\n  /** Called after link is removed */\n  onLinkRemove?: () => void;\n  /** Plugin slot: extra actions rendered inside the link input form */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nBehavior (extracted from current implementation):\n- Escape to cancel (cleans up phantom `#` placeholder links)\n- Click-outside to submit\n- Submit on Enter\n- Unlink button when link exists\n- Responds to `add-link` event from the editor event bus\n\nData attributes: `data-re-link-selector`, `data-has-link`, `data-open`\n\n## Styling\n\n### Approach: Unstyled + optional functional CSS\n\nComponents render with zero visual styles. Every component exposes `data-*` attributes and `className` props.\n\nAn optional `bubble-menu.css` ships with minimal functional CSS:\n- Flex layout for groups and item rows\n- Basic gap/padding so items don't collapse\n- Popover positioning helpers for NodeSelector\n- No colors, borders, hover states, or visual design\n\nUsers import it optionally:\n```tsx\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/bubble-menu.css';\n```\n\nOr style everything themselves via:\n- `className` props (Tailwind, CSS modules, etc.)\n- CSS targeting `data-*` attributes\n- Inline styles\n\n### Data attribute reference\n\n| Attribute | Component | Values |\n|-----------|-----------|--------|\n| `data-re-bubble-menu` | Root | - |\n| `data-re-bubble-menu-group` | Group | - |\n| `data-re-bubble-menu-separator` | Separator | - |\n| `data-re-bubble-menu-item` | Item | - |\n| `data-item` | Item, pre-wired items | `\"bold\"`, `\"italic\"`, etc. |\n| `data-active` | Item | present when active |\n| `data-re-node-selector` | NodeSelector | - |\n| `data-re-node-selector-item` | NodeSelector items | - |\n| `data-re-link-selector` | LinkSelector | - |\n| `data-open` | NodeSelector, LinkSelector | present when open |\n| `data-has-link` | LinkSelector | present when link exists |\n\n## Event bus integration\n\nThe editor event bus pattern (`EditorEventBus` from `core/event-bus.ts`) carries over to the open-source version. `BubbleMenu.Root` listens for `add-link` and programmatically opens the `LinkSelector`.\n\nThis enables cross-component communication (e.g., a keyboard shortcut triggering the link input) without prop drilling.\n\n## Usage examples\n\n### Minimal\n\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/bubble-menu.css';\n\n<BubbleMenu.Root>\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n    <BubbleMenu.Underline />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n### Resend dashboard consumption\n\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\nimport { VariablesDropdown } from '../plugins/variables/dropdown';\n\n<BubbleMenu.Root\n  excludeNodes={['image', 'button', 'htmlContent', 'socialLinks', 'youtube', 'twitter']}\n  className=\"bg-background rounded-xl border border-gray-3 shadow-xl\"\n>\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector className=\"...\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector\n    validateUrl={(value) => {\n      if (VARIABLE_PATTERN.test(value)) return value;\n      return getUrlFromString(value);\n    }}\n  >\n    <VariablesDropdown onVariableSelect={handleVariableSelect} modal>\n      <button className=\"...\">\n        <IconVariable className=\"size-4\" />\n      </button>\n    </VariablesDropdown>\n  </BubbleMenu.LinkSelector>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Underline className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Strike className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Code className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Uppercase className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignLeft className=\"p-2 text-gray-9 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignCenter className=\"p-2 text-gray-9 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignRight className=\"p-2 text-gray-9 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n### Custom item (user extending)\n\n```tsx\n<BubbleMenu.Group>\n  <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n  <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n  <BubbleMenu.Item\n    name=\"highlight\"\n    isActive={editor.isActive('highlight')}\n    onCommand={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleHighlight().run()}\n  >\n    <HighlightIcon className=\"h-4 w-4\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Item>\n</BubbleMenu.Group>\n```\n\n## Migration path\n\nAfter extraction, `dashboard/src/components/editor-v2/ui/bubble-menu/` gets replaced with a single composition file that imports from `@react-email/editor` and applies Resend's styles + injects `VariablesDropdown`.\n\nCurrent 6 files -> 1 composition file.\n\n## Decisions log\n\n| Decision | Choice | Reasoning |\n|----------|--------|-----------|\n| Approach | Compound components (Radix-style) | Strongest foundation for layering. Composition IS the API |\n| Scope | Text bubble menu only | Start small, iterate. Link/image/button menus follow same pattern later |\n| Package | `@react-email/editor` (same package) | Co-located with extensions. Single install for users |\n| Radix dependency | Peer dep | Aligns with philosophy, keeps bundle opt-in |\n| Icons | `lucide-react` as peer dep | Already used in dashboard, simplest API for defaults |\n| Event bus | Keep in OSS version | Enables cross-component communication (e.g., keyboard shortcut -> open link input) |\n| NodeSelector styling | Minimal functional CSS (optional) | Flex layout + positioning only. No visual design. Opt-in import |\n| Default composition | Primitives only for now | Build foundation right. Pre-composed defaults in follow-up |\n",
