            "content": "# Bubble Menu Compound Components Design\n\n## Context\n\nThe Resend dashboard editor V2 (`dashboard/src/components/editor-v2/`) has a bubble menu system that appears on text selection. We're extracting the text formatting bubble menu into `@react-email/editor` as an open-source compound component primitive, following a Radix UI-inspired architecture.\n\nThe goal: provide unstyled, composable building blocks that give developers full control over their bubble menu UI while encapsulating the complex TipTap positioning/visibility logic.\n\n### Layering model\n\n```\nLayer 0: Primitives (unstyled, composable, data-attributes) <-- this design\n   |\nLayer 1: Default compositions (pre-assembled, optional import) <-- future\n   |\nLayer 2: Themed/styled versions (CSS themes) <-- future\n```\n\nLayer 0 is the foundation. Nothing prevents shipping layers 1 and 2 later as compositions of the same primitives.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Text formatting bubble menu only (not link/image/button bubble menus)\n- Primitives only (no pre-composed defaults yet)\n- Ships in existing `@react-email/editor` package\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Approach: Compound components (Radix UI-inspired)\n\nEach sub-component is a standalone primitive. `BubbleMenu.Root` handles the hard parts (TipTap positioning, selection detection, visibility logic). Children are simple UI buttons that dispatch editor commands.\n\nRejected alternatives:\n- **Headless hook + default component (Base UI-style)**: `slotProps` becomes unnecessary when compound components let you compose directly. The composition IS the API.\n- **Configurable component + recipes (shadcn/ui-style)**: Tailwind dependency for defaults, copy-paste recipes diverge from source, less composable for structural changes.\n\n### File structure\n\n```\npackages/editor/src/\n  index.ts                          # add ui re-exports\n  ui/\n    index.ts                        # barrel: export * from './bubble-menu'\n    bubble-menu/\n      index.ts                      # barrel for all compound components\n      bubble-menu.css               # minimal functional CSS (layout/positioning only)\n      context.tsx                   # BubbleMenuContext (shared state)\n      root.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Root\n      group.tsx                     # BubbleMenu.Group\n      separator.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Separator\n      item.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Item (generic toggle)\n      bold.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Bold (pre-wired)\n      italic.tsx                    # BubbleMenu.Italic\n      underline.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Underline\n      strike.tsx                    # BubbleMenu.Strike\n      code.tsx                      # BubbleMenu.Code\n      uppercase.tsx                 # BubbleMenu.Uppercase\n      align-left.tsx                # BubbleMenu.AlignLeft\n      align-center.tsx              # BubbleMenu.AlignCenter\n      align-right.tsx               # BubbleMenu.AlignRight\n      node-selector.tsx             # BubbleMenu.NodeSelector\n      link-selector.tsx             # BubbleMenu.LinkSelector\n```\n\n### New dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|-----------|------|--------|\n| `@radix-ui/react-popover` | peer | NodeSelector dropdown |\n| `lucide-react` | peer | Default icons for pre-wired items |\n\nBoth already used in the dashboard - zero new weight for Resend.\n\n## Component API\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Root`\n\nWraps TipTap's `BubbleMenu` from `@tiptap/react/menus`. Provides context to children. Handles show/hide logic and event bus integration.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuRootProps {\n  /** Nodes that should NOT trigger the bubble menu */\n  excludeNodes?: string[];\n  /** TipTap BubbleMenu placement */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from selection in px */\n  offset?: number;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nInternal responsibilities:\n- Wraps `<BubbleMenu>` from `@tiptap/react/menus`\n- Reads editor via `useCurrentEditor()`\n- Provides `BubbleMenuContext` with: `editor`, `onHide` callback\n- Listens to `editorEventBus.on('add-link')` to programmatically open link selector\n- Default `shouldShow`: returns `false` for nodes in `excludeNodes`, returns `true` when selection content size > 0\n\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Group`\n\nVisual grouping container for related items.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuGroupProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: `<div role=\"group\">`\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-group`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Separator`\n\nDivider between groups.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuSeparatorProps {\n  className?: string;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: `<div role=\"separator\">`\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-separator`\n\n### `BubbleMenu.Item`\n\nGeneric toggle button primitive. Used directly for custom items, or internally by pre-wired items.\n\n```tsx\ninterface BubbleMenuItemProps {\n  /** Used for aria-label and data attribute */\n  name: string;\n  /** Whether this item is currently active */\n  isActive: boolean;\n  /** Called when clicked */\n  onCommand: () => void;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders: `<button type=\"button\" aria-label={name} aria-pressed={isActive}>`\nData attributes: `data-re-bubble-menu-item`, `data-item={name}`, `data-active` when pressed\n\n### Pre-wired items\n\n`BubbleMenu.Bold`, `Italic`, `Underline`, `Strike`, `Code`, `Uppercase`, `AlignLeft`, `AlignCenter`, `AlignRight`\n\n```tsx\ninterface PreWiredItemProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Override the default icon */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nEach reads editor from context, auto-wires `isActive` and `command`. Renders default lucide icon if no children. Internally delegates to `BubbleMenu.Item`.\n\nData attributes: inherit from `Item` + `data-item=\"bold\"` (etc.)\n\n### `BubbleMenu.NodeSelector`\n\nBlock type dropdown