 or visual design\n\nUsers import it optionally:\n```tsx\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/bubble-menu.css';\n```\n\nOr style everything themselves via:\n- `className` props (Tailwind, CSS modules, etc.)\n- CSS targeting `data-*` attributes\n- Inline styles\n\n### Data attribute reference\n\n| Attribute | Component | Values |\n|-----------|-----------|--------|\n| `data-re-bubble-menu` | Root | - |\n| `data-re-bubble-menu-group` | Group | - |\n| `data-re-bubble-menu-separator` | Separator | - |\n| `data-re-bubble-menu-item` | Item | - |\n| `data-item` | Item, pre-wired items | `\"bold\"`, `\"italic\"`, etc. |\n| `data-active` | Item | present when active |\n| `data-re-node-selector` | NodeSelector | - |\n| `data-re-node-selector-item` | NodeSelector items | - |\n| `data-re-link-selector` | LinkSelector | - |\n| `data-open` | NodeSelector, LinkSelector | present when open |\n| `data-has-link` | LinkSelector | present when link exists |\n\n## Event bus integration\n\nThe editor event bus pattern (`EditorEventBus` from `core/event-bus.ts`) carries over to the open-source version. `BubbleMenu.Root` listens for `add-link` and programmatically opens the `LinkSelector`.\n\nThis enables cross-component communication (e.g., a keyboard shortcut triggering the link input) without prop drilling.\n\n## Usage examples\n\n### Minimal\n\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/bubble-menu.css';\n\n<BubbleMenu.Root>\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n    <BubbleMenu.Underline />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n### Resend dashboard consumption\n\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\nimport { VariablesDropdown } from '../plugins/variables/dropdown';\n\n<BubbleMenu.Root\n  excludeNodes={['image', 'button', 'htmlContent', 'socialLinks', 'youtube', 'twitter']}\n  className=\"bg-background rounded-xl border border-gray-3 shadow-xl\"\n>\n  <BubbleMenu.NodeSelector className=\"...\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.LinkSelector\n    validateUrl={(value) => {\n      if (VARIABLE_PATTERN.test(value)) return value;\n      return getUrlFromString(value);\n    }}\n  >\n    <VariablesDropdown onVariableSelect={handleVariableSelect} modal>\n      <button className=\"...\">\n        <IconVariable className=\"size-4\" />\n      </button>\n    </VariablesDropdown>\n  </BubbleMenu.LinkSelector>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.Bold className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Italic className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Underline className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Strike className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Code className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.Uppercase className=\"p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n  <BubbleMenu.Separator className=\"border-gray-3\" />\n  <BubbleMenu.Group>\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignLeft className=\"p-2 text-gray-9 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignCenter className=\"p-2 text-gray-9 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n    <BubbleMenu.AlignRight className=\"p-2 text-gray-9 hover:bg-gray-a2\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Group>\n</BubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n### Custom item (user extending)\n\n```tsx\n<BubbleMenu.Group>\n  <BubbleMenu.Bold />\n  <BubbleMenu.Italic />\n  <BubbleMenu.Item\n    name=\"highlight\"\n    isActive={editor.isActive('highlight')}\n    onCommand={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleHighlight().run()}\n  >\n    <HighlightIcon className=\"h-4 w-4\" />\n  </BubbleMenu.Item>\n</BubbleMenu.Group>\n```\n\n## Migration path\n\nAfter extraction, `dashboard/src/components/editor-v2/ui/bubble-menu/` gets replaced with a single composition file that imports from `@react-email/editor` and applies Resend's styles + injects `VariablesDropdown`.\n\nCurrent 6 files -> 1 composition file.\n\n## Decisions log\n\n| Decision | Choice | Reasoning |\n|----------|--------|-----------|\n| Approach | Compound components (Radix-style) | Strongest foundation for layering. Composition IS the API |\n| Scope | Text bubble menu only | Start small, iterate. Link/image/button menus follow same pattern later |\n| Package | `@react-email/editor` (same package) | Co-located with extensions. Single install for users |\n| Radix dependency | Peer dep | Aligns with philosophy, keeps bundle opt-in |\n| Icons | `lucide-react` as peer dep | Already used in dashboard, simplest API for defaults |\n| Event bus | Keep in OSS version | Enables cross-component communication (e.g., keyboard shortcut -> open link input) |\n| NodeSelector styling | Minimal functional CSS (optional) | Flex layout + positioning only. No visual design. Opt-in import |\n| Default composition | Primitives only for now | Build foundation right. Pre-composed defaults in follow-up |\n",
