            "content": "# Bubble Menu Compound Components Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Add Radix-inspired compound component primitives for a text formatting bubble menu to `@react-email/editor`.\n\n**Architecture:** Compound components where `BubbleMenu.Root` wraps TipTap's positioning/visibility logic and provides context. Children are unstyled UI primitives (buttons, groups, separators) that dispatch editor commands via the context. An event bus enables cross-component communication. All components expose `data-*` attributes and `className` props for styling.\n\n**Tech Stack:** React, TipTap v3 (`@tiptap/react`, `@tiptap/react/menus`), `@radix-ui/react-popover` (peer), `lucide-react` (peer), Vitest, tsdown.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add peer dependencies and package exports\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `packages/editor/package.json`\n\n**Step 1: Update package.json**\n\nAdd `@radix-ui/react-popover` and `lucide-react` as peer deps. Add `@tiptap/extension-underline` as a dependency (needed for Uppercase detection). Add new export path for styles.\n\nIn `packages/editor/package.json`, add to `peerDependencies`:\n```json\n\"@radix-ui/react-popover\": \"^1.0.0\",\n\"lucide-react\": \">=0.300.0\"\n```\n\nAdd a new export entry for the CSS file:\n```json\n\"./styles/bubble-menu.css\": \"./dist/ui/bubble-menu/bubble-menu.css\"\n```\n\n**Step 2: Install deps and verify**\n\nRun: `pnpm install` (from react-email root)\nExpected: lockfile updates, no errors\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/package.json pnpm-lock.yaml\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add peer deps for bubble menu (radix, lucide)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Event bus and core types\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/event-bus.ts`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/types.ts`\n- Test: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/event-bus.spec.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the event bus test**\n\n```typescript\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/event-bus.spec.ts\nimport { editorBubbleMenuEventBus } from './event-bus';\n\ndescribe('editorBubbleMenuEventBus', () => {\n  it('dispatches and receives events', () => {\n    const handler = vi.fn();\n    const sub = editorBubbleMenuEventBus.on('add-link', handler);\n\n    editorBubbleMenuEventBus.dispatch('add-link', undefined);\n\n    expect(handler).toHaveBeenCalledOnce();\n    sub.unsubscribe();\n  });\n\n  it('unsubscribes correctly', () => {\n    const handler = vi.fn();\n    const sub = editorBubbleMenuEventBus.on('add-link', handler);\n    sub.unsubscribe();\n\n    editorBubbleMenuEventBus.dispatch('add-link', undefined);\n\n    expect(handler).not.toHaveBeenCalled();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/event-bus.spec.ts` (from react-email root)\nExpected: FAIL - module not found\n\n**Step 3: Implement types and event bus**\n\n```typescript\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/types.ts\n\n/**\n * Event map for the bubble menu event bus.\n * Extensible via TypeScript module augmentation.\n */\nexport interface BubbleMenuEventMap {\n  'add-link': undefined;\n}\n\nexport type BubbleMenuEventName = keyof BubbleMenuEventMap;\n\nexport type BubbleMenuEventHandler<T extends BubbleMenuEventName> = (\n  payload: BubbleMenuEventMap[T],\n) => void | Promise<void>;\n\nexport interface BubbleMenuEventSubscription {\n  unsubscribe: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n```typescript\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/event-bus.ts\nimport type {\n  BubbleMenuEventHandler,\n  BubbleMenuEventMap,\n  BubbleMenuEventName,\n  BubbleMenuEventSubscription,\n} from './types';\n\nconst EVENT_PREFIX = '@react-email/editor:bubble-menu:';\n\nclass BubbleMenuEventBus {\n  private prefixEventName(eventName: BubbleMenuEventName): string {\n    return `${EVENT_PREFIX}${eventName}`;\n  }\n\n  dispatch<T extends BubbleMenuEventName>(\n    eventName: T,\n    payload: BubbleMenuEventMap[T],\n    options?: { target?: EventTarget },\n  ): void {\n    const target = options?.target ?? window;\n    const prefixedEventName = this.prefixEventName(eventName);\n    const event = new CustomEvent(prefixedEventName, {\n      detail: payload,\n      bubbles: false,\n      cancelable: false,\n    });\n    target.dispatchEvent(event);\n  }\n\n  on<T extends BubbleMenuEventName>(\n    eventName: T,\n    handler: BubbleMenuEventHandler<T>,\n    options?: AddEventListenerOptions & { target?: EventTarget },\n  ): BubbleMenuEventSubscription {\n    const target = options?.target ?? window;\n    const prefixedEventName = this.prefixEventName(eventName);\n    const abortController = new AbortController();\n\n    const wrappedHandler = (event: Event) => {\n      const customEvent = event as CustomEvent<BubbleMenuEventMap[T]>;\n      handler(customEvent.detail);\n    };\n\n    target.addEventListener(prefixedEventName, wrappedHandler, {\n      ...options,\n      signal: abortController.signal,\n    });\n\n    return {\n      unsubscribe: () => {\n        abortController.abort();\n      },\n    };\n  }\n}\n\nexport const editorBubbleMenuEventBus = new BubbleMenuEventBus();\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/event-bus.spec.ts`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add bubble menu event bus and types\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: BubbleMenuContext\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/context.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Implement context**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/context.tsx\nimport type { Editor } from '@tiptap/core';\nimport * as React from 'react';\n\nexport interface BubbleMenuContextValue {\n  editor: Editor;\n}\n\nexport const BubbleMenuContext =\n  React.createContext<BubbleMenuContextValue | null>(null);\n\nexport function useBubbleMenuContext(): BubbleMenuContextValue {\n  const context = React.useContext(BubbleMenuContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\n      'BubbleMenu compound components must be used within <BubbleMenu.Root>',\n    );\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/context.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add BubbleMenuContext\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: BubbleMenu.Root\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.tsx`\n- Test: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write test**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx\nimport { render } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { BubbleMenuRoot } from './root';\n\n// BubbleMenu.Root requires EditorContext from TipTap which is hard to mock in isolation.\n// Test the component renders null when no editor is available.\ndescribe('BubbleMenuRoot', () => {\n  it('renders null when no editor context is available', () => {\n    const { container } = render(\n      <BubbleMenuRoot>\n        <div>child</div>\n      </BubbleMenuRoot>,\n    );\n    expect(container.innerHTML).toBe('');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL - module not found\n\n**Step 3: Implement Root**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.tsx\nimport { useCurrentEditor, useEditorState } from '@tiptap/react';\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@tiptap/react/menus';\nimport * as React from 'react';\nimport { BubbleMenuContext } from './context';\nimport { editorBubbleMenuEventBus } from './event-bus';\n\nexport interface BubbleMenuRootProps {\n  /** Node types that should NOT trigger the bubble menu */\n  excludeNodes?: string[];\n  /** Placement relative to selection */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from selection in px */\n  offset?: number;\n  /** Additional className on the outer wrapper */\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function BubbleMenuRoot({\n  excludeNodes = [],\n  placement = 'bottom',\n  offset = 8,\n  className,\n  children,\n}: BubbleMenuRootProps) {\n  const { editor } = useCurrentEditor();\n\n  if (!editor) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <BubbleMenu\n      editor={editor}\n      data-re-bubble-menu=\"\"\n      shouldShow={({ editor, view }) => {\n        for (const node of excludeNodes) {\n          if (editor.isActive(node)) {\n            return false;\n          }\n        }\n        if (view.dom.classList.contains('dragging')) {\n          return false;\n        }\n        return editor.view.state.selection.content().size > 0;\n      }}\n      options={{\n        placement,\n        offset,\n      }}\n      className={className}\n    >\n      <BubbleMenuContext.Provider value={{ editor }}>\n        {children}\n      </BubbleMenuContext.Provider>\n    </BubbleMenu>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nNote: We need `@testing-library/react` as a devDependency. Add it to `packages/editor/package.json`:\n```json\n\"devDependencies\": {\n  \"@testing-library/react\": \"^16.0.0\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm install && pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx packages/editor/package.json pnpm-lock.yaml\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add BubbleMenu.Root component\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: BubbleMenu.Group and BubbleMenu.Separator\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/separator.tsx`\n- Test: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write test**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.spec.tsx\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { BubbleMenuGroup } from './group';\nimport { BubbleMenuSeparator } from './separator';\n\ndescribe('BubbleMenuGroup', () => {\n  it('renders children with correct data attribute and role', () => {\n    render(\n      <BubbleMenuGroup>\n        <button>Bold</button>\n      </BubbleMenuGroup>,\n    );\n    const group = screen.getByRole('group');\n    expect(group).toBeDefined();\n    expect(group.dataset.reBubbleMenuGroup).toBeDefined();\n    expect(group.textContent).toBe('Bold');\n  });\n\n  it('applies className', () => {\n    render(\n      <BubbleMenuGroup className=\"custom-class\">\n        <button>Bold</button>\n      </BubbleMenuGroup>,\n    );\n    const group = screen.getByRole('group');\n    expect(group.className).toBe('custom-class');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('BubbleMenuSeparator', () => {\n  it('renders a separator with correct data attribute', () => {\n    render(<BubbleMenuSeparator />);\n    const separator = screen.getByRole('separator');\n    expect(separator).toBeDefined();\n    expect(separator.dataset.reBubbleMenuSeparator).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('applies className', () => {\n    render(<BubbleMenuSeparator className=\"divider\" />);\n    const separator = screen.getByRole('separator');\n    expect(separator.className).toBe('divider');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL\n\n**Step 3: Implement Group and Separator**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.tsx\nimport * as React from 'react';\n\nexport interface BubbleMenuGroupProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function BubbleMenuGroup({ className, children }: BubbleMenuGroupProps) {\n  return (\n    <div role=\"group\" className={className} data-re-bubble-menu-group=\"\">\n      {children}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/separator.tsx\nimport * as React from 'react';\n\nexport interface BubbleMenuSeparatorProps {\n  className?: string;\n}\n\nexport function BubbleMenuSeparator({ className }: BubbleMenuSeparatorProps) {\n  return (\n    <div role=\"separator\" className={className} data-re-bubble-menu-separator=\"\" />\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/separator.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/group.spec.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add BubbleMenu.Group and BubbleMenu.Separator\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: BubbleMenu.Item (generic toggle)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.tsx`\n- Test: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write test**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.spec.tsx\nimport { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { BubbleMenuItem } from './item';\n\ndescribe('BubbleMenuItem', () => {\n  it('renders a button with correct aria attributes when inactive', () => {\n    const onCommand = vi.fn();\n    render(\n      <BubbleMenuItem name=\"bold\" isActive={false} onCommand={onCommand}>\n        <span>B</span>\n      </BubbleMenuItem>,\n    );\n\n    const button = screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'bold' });\n    expect(button).toBeDefined();\n    expect(button.getAttribute('aria-pressed')).toBe('false');\n    expect(button.dataset.reBubbleMenuItem).toBeDefined();\n    expect(button.dataset.item).toBe('bold');\n    expect(button.dataset.active).toBeUndefined();\n  });\n\n  it('sets data-active and aria-pressed when active', () => {\n    render(\n      <BubbleMenuItem name=\"bold\" isActive={true} onCommand={() => {}}>\n        <span>B</span>\n      </BubbleMenuItem>,\n    );\n\n    const button = screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'bold' });\n    expect(button.getAttribute('aria-pressed')).toBe('true');\n    expect(button.dataset.active).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('calls onCommand on click', () => {\n    const onCommand = vi.fn();\n    render(\n      <BubbleMenuItem name=\"bold\" isActive={false} onCommand={onCommand}>\n        <span>B</span>\n      </BubbleMenuItem>,\n    );\n\n    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'bold' }));\n    expect(onCommand).toHaveBeenCalledOnce();\n  });\n\n  it('applies className', () => {\n    render(\n      <BubbleMenuItem name=\"bold\" isActive={false} onCommand={() => {}} className=\"custom\">\n        <span>B</span>\n      </BubbleMenuItem>,\n    );\n\n    expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'bold' }).className).toBe('custom');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL\n\n**Step 3: Implement Item**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.tsx\nimport * as React from 'react';\n\nexport interface BubbleMenuItemProps {\n  /** Used for aria-label and data-item attribute */\n  name: string;\n  /** Whether this item is currently active */\n  isActive: boolean;\n  /** Called when clicked */\n  onCommand: () => void;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function BubbleMenuItem({\n  name,\n  isActive,\n  onCommand,\n  className,\n  children,\n}: BubbleMenuItemProps) {\n  return (\n    <button\n      type=\"button\"\n      aria-label={name}\n      aria-pressed={isActive}\n      className={className}\n      data-re-bubble-menu-item=\"\"\n      data-item={name}\n      {...(isActive ? { 'data-active': '' } : {})}\n      onClick={onCommand}\n    >\n      {children}\n    </button>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm vitest run packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/item.spec.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add BubbleMenu.Item primitive\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Pre-wired formatting items (Bold, Italic, Underline, Strike, Code, Uppercase)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/bold.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/italic.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/underline.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/strike.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/code.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/uppercase.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/create-pre-wired-item.tsx` (shared factory)\n\n**Step 1: Implement shared factory**\n\nAll pre-wired items follow the same pattern: read editor from context, check `isActive`, run a toggle command, render a default icon. A factory avoids duplication.\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/create-pre-wired-item.tsx\nimport { useEditorState } from '@tiptap/react';\nimport type { LucideIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport * as React from 'react';\nimport { useBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\nimport { BubbleMenuItem } from './item';\n\nexport interface PreWiredItemProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Override the default icon */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\ninterface PreWiredItemConfig {\n  name: string;\n  /** TipTap mark/node name to check isActive */\n  activeName: string;\n  /** Additional isActive params (e.g., { level: 1 } for headings) */\n  activeParams?: Record<string, unknown>;\n  /** Editor chain command name (e.g., 'toggleBold') */\n  command: string;\n  /** Default icon component from lucide-react */\n  icon: LucideIcon;\n}\n\nexport function createPreWiredItem(config: PreWiredItemConfig) {\n  function PreWiredItem({ className, children }: PreWiredItemProps) {\n    const { editor } = useBubbleMenuContext();\n    const Icon = config.icon;\n\n    const isActive = useEditorState({\n      editor,\n      selector: ({ editor }) => {\n        if (config.activeParams) {\n          return editor?.isActive(config.activeName, config.activeParams) ?? false;\n        }\n        return editor?.isActive(config.activeName) ?? false;\n      },\n    });\n\n    const handleCommand = () => {\n      const chain = editor.chain().focus();\n      const method = (chain as unknown as Record<string, () => typeof chain>)[config.command];\n      if (method) {\n        method.call(chain).run();\n      }\n    };\n\n    return (\n      <BubbleMenuItem\n        name={config.name}\n        isActive={isActive}\n        onCommand={handleCommand}\n        className={className}\n      >\n        {children ?? <Icon />}\n      </BubbleMenuItem>\n    );\n  }\n\n  PreWiredItem.displayName = `BubbleMenu${config.name.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + config.name.slice(1)}`;\n\n  return PreWiredItem;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create all pre-wired items**\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/bold.tsx\nimport { BoldIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { createPreWiredItem } from './create-pre-wired-item';\n\nexport const BubbleMenuBold = createPreWiredItem({\n  name: 'bold',\n  activeName: 'bold',\n  command: 'toggleBold',\n  icon: BoldIcon,\n});\n```\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/italic.tsx\nimport { ItalicIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { createPreWiredItem } from './create-pre-wired-item';\n\nexport const BubbleMenuItalic = createPreWiredItem({\n  name: 'italic',\n  activeName: 'italic',\n  command: 'toggleItalic',\n  icon: ItalicIcon,\n});\n```\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/underline.tsx\nimport { UnderlineIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { createPreWiredItem } from './create-pre-wired-item';\n\nexport const BubbleMenuUnderline = createPreWiredItem({\n  name: 'underline',\n  activeName: 'underline',\n  command: 'toggleUnderline',\n  icon: UnderlineIcon,\n});\n```\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/strike.tsx\nimport { StrikethroughIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { createPreWiredItem } from './create-pre-wired-item';\n\nexport const BubbleMenuStrike = createPreWiredItem({\n  name: 'strike',\n  activeName: 'strike',\n  command: 'toggleStrike',\n  icon: StrikethroughIcon,\n});\n```\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/code.tsx\nimport { CodeIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { createPreWiredItem } from './create-pre-wired-item';\n\nexport const BubbleMenuCode = createPreWiredItem({\n  name: 'code',\n  activeName: 'code',\n  command: 'toggleCode',\n  icon: CodeIcon,\n});\n```\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/uppercase.tsx\nimport { CaseUpperIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { createPreWiredItem } from './create-pre-wired-item';\n\nexport const BubbleMenuUppercase = createPreWiredItem({\n  name: 'uppercase',\n  activeName: 'uppercase',\n  command: 'toggleUppercase',\n  icon: CaseUpperIcon,\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/create-pre-wired-item.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/bold.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/italic.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/underline.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/strike.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/code.tsx packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/uppercase.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat(editor): add pre-wired formatting items (bold, italic, underline, strike, code, uppercase)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Pre-wired alignment items (AlignLeft, AlignCenter, AlignRight)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/align-left.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/align-center.tsx`\n- Create: `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/align-right.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Implement alignment items**\n\nAlignment items are slightly different: they use `editor.isActive({ alignment: 'left' })` and `editor.commands.setAlignment('left')` rather than toggle commands.\n\n```tsx\n// packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/align-left.tsx\nimport { useEditorState } from '@tiptap/react';\nimport { AlignLeftIcon } from 'lucide-r