            "content": "# Add pre-composed BubbleMenu.Default component (Layer 1)\n\n## Context\n\nLayer 0 bubble menu primitives are shipped in `@react-email/editor@0.0.0-experimental.7` (PR #2987, merged). This is Layer 1 — a single-import, batteries-included bubble menu that composes all Layer 0 primitives into one ready-to-use component.\n\n## Goal\n\n```tsx\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\n\n// Zero-config — renders everything with sensible defaults\n<BubbleMenu.Default />\n\n// Customizable — exclude specific items\n<BubbleMenu.Default excludeItems={['uppercase', 'code', 'align-left']} />\n\n// Forward Root props\n<BubbleMenu.Default excludeNodes={['image', 'button']} placement=\"top\" />\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Component API\n\nCreate `BubbleMenuDefault` exported as both a named export and as `BubbleMenu.Default` on the compound namespace.\n\n```ts\nexport interface BubbleMenuDefaultProps {\n  /** Items to exclude from the bubble menu by name */\n  excludeItems?: Array<\n    | 'bold' | 'italic' | 'underline' | 'strike' | 'code' | 'uppercase'\n    | 'align-left' | 'align-center' | 'align-right'\n    | 'node-selector' | 'link-selector'\n  >;\n  /** Node types that should NOT trigger the bubble menu (forwarded to Root) */\n  excludeNodes?: string[];\n  /** Placement relative to selection (forwarded to Root, default: 'bottom') */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from selection in px (forwarded to Root, default: 8) */\n  offset?: number;\n  /** Called when the bubble menu hides (forwarded to Root) */\n  onHide?: () => void;\n  /** className applied to the Root wrapper */\n  className?: string;\n}\n```\n\n### Internal composition\n\n`BubbleMenu.Default` must compose the following Layer 0 primitives internally, in this order:\n\n1. **`BubbleMenu.Root`** — wraps everything, receives `excludeNodes`, `placement`, `offset`, `onHide`, `className`\n2. **`BubbleMenu.NodeSelector`** — the one-shot convenience component (NOT the decomposed compound). Uses internal uncontrolled state. Rendered unless `excludeItems` contains `'node-selector'`\n3. **`BubbleMenu.LinkSelector`** — the OSS link selector. Rendered unless `excludeItems` contains `'link-selector'`\n4. **`BubbleMenu.ItemGroup`** containing formatting marks: Bold, Italic, Underline, Strike, Code, Uppercase — each excluded if its name appears in `excludeItems`. The entire group is omitted if all 6 are excluded\n5. **`BubbleMenu.ItemGroup`** containing alignment items: AlignLeft, AlignCenter, AlignRight — each excluded if its name appears in `excludeItems`. The entire group is omitted if all 3 are excluded\n\n### Behavior details\n\n- **NodeSelector `omit` passthrough**: when `excludeItems` contains node type names that match `NodeType` values (e.g. `'Text'`, `'Title'`, `'Code'`), those should be forwarded as the `omit` prop on `NodeSelector`. But the `excludeItems` values for mark/alignment items use lowercase kebab-case (e.g. `'bold'`, `'align-left'`), while NodeType values use title case (e.g. `'Text'`, `'Title'`). To avoid confusion, `excludeItems` should NOT support excluding individual node types — that's a Layer 0 concern. If the consumer wants to exclude specific node types, they should drop down to Layer 0 composition.\n- **State coordination**: the Default component must manage the mutual exclusion between NodeSelector and LinkSelector (opening one closes the other). This requires internal state for both `isNodeSelectorOpen` and `isLinkSelectorOpen`, plus passing `onHide` to reset both. Since we're using the one-shot `BubbleMenu.NodeSelector` (not decomposed), we need to use its `open` and `onOpenChange` props for controlled state.\n- **Event bus**: `BubbleMenu.LinkSelector` already subscribes to `bubble-menu:add-link` internally, so no extra wiring is needed.\n- **No `children` prop**: this is a sealed composition. Consumers who need custom content should use Layer 0 primitives directly.\n- **No styling**: the component is unstyled