          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Good. Option 1 with shared internals. Let me check exactly what can be shared before presenting the design.\n\nThe shared code between the two would be:\n- `getUrlFromString` (URL validation/normalization) — already in `utils.ts`\n- `setLinkHref` / `focusEditor` helpers — already in `link-selector.tsx`\n- The safe protocol set\n\nThe dedicated parts for `LinkBubbleMenu.Form`:\n- Prefills with the current link's href\n- `extendMarkRange('link')` before setting href (collapsed cursor)\n- No `bubble-menu:add-link` subscription\n- No toggle button at all\n\nLet me present the design section by section.\n\n---\n\n## Design: Link Bubble Menu Primitives\n\n### Architecture overview\n\nA new compound component namespace `LinkBubbleMenu` that follows the same Radix-inspired pattern as the text `BubbleMenu`. The link bubble menu shows when the cursor is collapsed inside a link node — it provides actions to edit, unlink, or open the link.\n\n**Compound namespace:**\n```\nLinkBubbleMenu.Root      — wraps TipTap BubbleMenu, shows on collapsed cursor inside link\nLinkBubbleMenu.Item      — reuses existing BubbleMenuItem\nLinkBubbleMenu.EditLink  — pre-wired: toggles edit form open\nLinkBubbleMenu.Unlink    — pre-wired: removes the link mark\nLinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink  — pre-wired: renders an <a> to the current href\nLinkBubbleMenu.Form      — inline URL editing form (input + apply/unlink buttons)\n```\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.Root`\n\nSimilar to `BubbleMenu.Root` but with different `shouldShow` logic:\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuRootProps {\n  onHide?: () => void;\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  offset?: number;\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\n`shouldShow`: `editor.isActive('link') && editor.view.state.selection.content().size === 0`\n\nProvides a `LinkBubbleMenuContext` with `{ editor, linkHref, isEditing, setIsEditing }` — the `isEditing` state controls the toolbar ↔ form swap. `linkHref` is derived from `editor.getAttributes('link').href` via `useEditorState`.\n\n### Pre-wired items\n\n- **`LinkBubbleMenu.EditLink`** — button that calls `setIsEditing(true)`. Default icon: `PencilIcon`.\n- **`LinkBubbleMenu.Unlink`** — button that calls `editor.chain().focus().unsetLink().run()`. Default icon: `UnlinkIcon`.\n- **`LinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink`** — renders an `<a href={linkHref} target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">` instead of a button. Default icon: `ExternalLinkIcon`.\n\nAll accept `className?: string` and `children?: React.ReactNode` (to override the icon).\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.Form`\n\nThe dedicated editing form. Reads `linkHref` from context to prefill. On submit, validates the URL using the shared `getUrlFromString` from `utils.ts`, then applies via `editor.chain().extendMarkRange('link').setLink({ href }).run()`. On empty submit, unlinks.\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuFormProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Custom URL validator (default: getUrlFromString) */\n  validateUrl?: (value: string) => string | null;\n  /** Called after link is applied */\n  onLinkApply?: (href: string) => void;\n  /** Called after link is removed */\n  onLinkRemove?: () => void;\n  /** Extra content inside the form (e.g. a variables dropdown) */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nHandles: Escape to cancel (closes form, calls `setIsEditing(false)`), click-outside auto-submits. Renders input + apply/unlink buttons with `data-re-*` attributes for styling.\n\n### Shared internals (no duplication)\n\nBoth `LinkBubbleMenu.Form` and the existing `BubbleMenu.LinkSelector` will import from `utils.ts`:\n- `getUrlFromString` — already there\n- `focusEditor` — extract from `link-selector.tsx` into `utils.ts`\n- `setLinkHref` — extract from `link-selector.tsx` into `utils.ts`\n\nThe `LinkSelector` gets refactored to import these from utils instead of defining them inline.\n\n### File structure\n\n```\npackages/editor/src/ui/link-bubble-menu/\n  root.tsx              — LinkBubbleMenuRoot\n  context.tsx           — LinkBubbleMenuContext + useLinkBubbleMenuContext\n  item.tsx              — re-exports BubbleMenuItem (or thin wrapper)\n  edit-link.tsx         — pre-wired edit button\n  unlink.tsx            — pre-wired unlink button\n  open-link.tsx         — pre-wired open-in-new-tab <a>\n  form.tsx              — URL editing form\n  index.ts              — compound namespace + exports\n```\n\nShared utils stay in `packages/editor/src/ui/bubble-menu/utils.ts` (already exists).\n\n### CSS / data attributes\n\nNew attributes following the existing pattern:\n- `data-re-link-bubble-menu` (Root)\n- `data-re-link-bubble-menu-item` (items)\n- `data-re-link-bubble-menu-form` (form wrapper)\n- `data-re-link-bubble-menu-input` (URL input)\n- `data-re-link-bubble-menu-apply` (apply button)\n- `data-re-link-bubble-menu-unlink` (unlink button in form)\n\nMinimal functional CSS added to `bubble-menu.css` (or a new `link-bubble-menu.css`).\n\n### Dashboard migration (PRODUCT-1512, future)\n\nThe dashboard's `EditorBubbleMenuLink` would become:\n\n```tsx\n<LinkBubbleMenu.Root onHide={() => setIsEditing(false)} className=\"...\">\n  {!isEditing ? (\n    <div className=\"...\">\n      <LinkBubbleMenu.EditLink className=\"...\" />\n      <LinkBubbleMenu.Unlink className=\"...\" />\n      <LinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink className=\"...\" />\n    </div>\n  ) : (\n    <LinkSelector isOpen={isEditing} setIsOpen={setIsEditing} showLinkLabel={false} />\n  )}\n</LinkBubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\nNote: the dashboard would still use its own `LinkSelector` for the form (with variables dropdown), but the Root + toolbar items come from OSS.\n\n---\n\nDoes this design look right so far? Anything you'd change before I write it up formally?",
