            "content": "# Link Bubble Menu Primitives — Design\n\nPRODUCT-1506\n\n## Context\n\nThe text formatting bubble menu primitives shipped in `@react-email/editor@0.0.0-experimental.7`. The dashboard has a second bubble menu — `EditorBubbleMenuLink` — that appears when the cursor is collapsed inside a link. It shows Edit/Unlink/Open actions and can swap to an inline URL editing form. This document covers extracting that into OSS compound component primitives.\n\n## Goal\n\n```tsx\nimport { LinkBubbleMenu } from '@react-email/editor';\n\n<LinkBubbleMenu.Root>\n  <LinkBubbleMenu.Toolbar>\n    <LinkBubbleMenu.EditLink className=\"...\" />\n    <LinkBubbleMenu.Unlink className=\"...\" />\n    <LinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink className=\"...\" />\n  </LinkBubbleMenu.Toolbar>\n  <LinkBubbleMenu.Form className=\"...\" />\n</LinkBubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n## Compound namespace\n\n```\nLinkBubbleMenu.Root       — TipTap BubbleMenu wrapper, shows on collapsed cursor inside link\nLinkBubbleMenu.Toolbar    — visible when NOT editing, hides when form is active\nLinkBubbleMenu.Form       — visible when editing, hides when toolbar is active\nLinkBubbleMenu.EditLink   — pre-wired button: enters edit mode\nLinkBubbleMenu.Unlink     — pre-wired button: removes the link mark\nLinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink   — pre-wired <a>: opens the link href in a new tab\n```\n\n## Component API\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.Root`\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuRootProps {\n  /** Called when the bubble menu hides */\n  onHide?: () => void;\n  /** Placement relative to cursor (default: 'bottom') */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from cursor in px (default: 8) */\n  offset?: number;\n  /** className on the outer wrapper */\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\n**shouldShow logic:** `editor.isActive('link') && editor.view.state.selection.content().size === 0`\n\n**Internal context (`LinkBubbleMenuContext`):**\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuContextValue {\n  editor: Editor;\n  linkHref: string;          // current link's href from editor state\n  isEditing: boolean;        // toolbar vs form mode\n  setIsEditing: (v: boolean) => void;\n}\n```\n\n`linkHref` is derived reactively via `useEditorState` reading `editor.getAttributes('link').href`. `isEditing` resets to `false` on `onHide`.\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.Toolbar`\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuToolbarProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders its children only when `isEditing === false`. Purely conditional rendering wrapper.\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.Form`\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuFormProps {\n  className?: string;\n  /** Custom URL validator (default: getUrlFromString) */\n  validateUrl?: (value: string) => string | null;\n  /** Called after link is applied */\n  onLinkApply?: (href: string) => void;\n  /** Called after link is removed */\n  onLinkRemove?: () => void;\n  /** Extra content inside the form (e.g. a variables dropdown slot) */\n  children?: React.ReactNode;\n}\n```\n\nRenders only when `isEditing === true`. Prefills the input with `linkHref` from context. On submit, validates URL and applies via shared `setLinkHref` helper. On empty submit or invalid URL, removes the link. Escape closes the form (sets `isEditing(false)`). Click-outside auto-submits.\n\nData attributes: `data-re-link-bm-form`, `data-re-link-bm-input`, `data-re-link-bm-apply`, `data-re-link-bm-unlink`.\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.EditLink`\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuEditLinkProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children?: React.ReactNode; // override default PencilIcon\n}\n```\n\nButton that sets `isEditing(true)`. Data attribute: `data-re-link-bm-item`, `data-item=\"edit-link\"`.\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.Unlink`\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuUnlinkProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children?: React.ReactNode; // override default UnlinkIcon\n}\n```\n\nButton that calls `editor.chain().focus().unsetLink().run()`. Data attribute: `data-re-link-bm-item`, `data-item=\"unlink\"`.\n\n### `LinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink`\n\n```ts\ninterface LinkBubbleMenuOpenLinkProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children?: React.ReactNode; // override default ExternalLinkIcon\n}\n```\n\nRenders an `<a href={linkHref} target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">`. Data attribute: `data-re-link-bm-item`, `data-item=\"open-link\"`.\n\n## Shared internals (avoiding duplication)\n\nThree helpers currently private in `link-selector.tsx` need to become shared exports in `utils.ts`:\n\n1. **`setLinkHref(editor, href)`** — handles empty href (unsets link), collapsed selection (`extendMarkRange`), and range selection (`setLink`). Already implemented correctly in `link-selector.tsx:241-259`.\n\n2. **`focusEditor(editor)`** — `setTimeout(() => editor.commands.focus(), 0)`. Already in `link-selector.tsx:261-264`.\n\n3. **`getUrlFromString(str)`** — already exported from `utils.ts`.\n\nAfter extraction, `link-selector.tsx` imports these from `utils.ts` instead of defining them inline. `LinkBubbleMenu.Form` also imports from `utils.ts`.\n\n## File structure\n\n```\npackages/editor/src/ui/\n  bubble-menu/\n    utils.ts              ← add setLinkHref, focusEditor exports\n    link-selector.tsx      ← refactor to import from utils.ts\n  link-bubble-menu/\n    context.tsx            ← LinkBubbleMenuContext + hook\n    root.tsx               ← LinkBubbleMenuRoot\n    toolbar.tsx            ← conditional wrapper (shows when !isEditing)\n    form.tsx               ← URL editing form\n    edit-link.tsx          ← pre-wired edit button\n    unlink.tsx             ← pre-wired unlink button\n    open-link.tsx          ← pre-wired open link <a>\n    link-bubble-menu.css   ← minimal layout CSS for data-re-link-bm-* attributes\n    index.ts               ← compound namespace + all exports\n```\n\nTop-level `src/ui/index.ts` and `src/index.ts` re-export the new namespace.\n\n## CSS / data attributes\n\nAll new attributes use the `data-re-link-bm-` prefix:\n\n| Element | Attribute |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Root | `data-re-link-bm` |\n| Toolbar items | `data-re-link-bm-item` + `data-item={name}` |\n| Form | `data-re-link-bm-form` |\n| Input | `data-re-link-bm-input` |\n| Apply button | `data-re-link-bm-apply` |\n| Unlink button (form) | `data-re-link-bm-unlink` |\n\nMinimal CSS in `link-bubble-menu.css` — layout only (flex, sizing), no visual design. Same pattern as `bubble-menu.css`.\n\n## Tests\n\nFile: `packages/editor/src/ui/link-bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx` (and others as needed)\n\nRequired test cases:\n- Root renders when link is active and selection is collapsed\n- Root does not render when no link is active\n- Root does not render when selection has content (non-collapsed)\n- Toolbar renders its children when `isEditing === false`\n- Toolbar hides when `isEditing === true`\n- Form renders when `isEditing === true`\n- Form hides when `isEditing === false`\n- EditLink sets isEditing to true on click\n- Unlink calls `editor.chain().focus().unsetLink().run()`\n- OpenLink renders an `<a>` with the correct href\n- Form prefills input with current link href\n- Form submits valid URL and applies link\n- Form clears link on empty submit\n- Form rejects invalid URLs\n- `onHide` resets isEditing to false\n\nShared util tests (additions to existing `utils.spec.ts`):\n- `setLinkHref` with empty href unsets link\n- `setLinkHref` with collapsed selection uses `extendMarkRange`\n- `setLinkHref` with range selection uses `setLink` directly\n- `focusEditor` calls `editor.commands.focus()`\n\n## Dashboard migration (future, PRODUCT-1512)\n\nThe dashboard's `EditorBubbleMenuLink` replaces its TipTap `<BubbleMenu>` with `<LinkBubbleMenu.Root>`, uses `.EditLink`, `.Unlink`, `.OpenLink` for the toolbar, and keeps its own `<LinkSelector>` for the form (Resend-specific variables dropdown, toast notifications):\n\n```tsx\n<LinkBubbleMenu.Root onHide={() => setIsEditing(false)} className=\"...\">\n  <LinkBubbleMenu.Toolbar className=\"...\">\n    <LinkBubbleMenu.EditLink className=\"...\" />\n    <LinkBubbleMenu.Unlink className=\"...\" />\n    <LinkBubbleMenu.OpenLink className=\"...\" />\n  </LinkBubbleMenu.Toolbar>\n  {isEditing && (\n    <LinkSelector\n      isOpen={isEditing}\n      setIsOpen={setIsEditing}\n      showLinkLabel={false}\n    />\n  )}\n</LinkBubbleMenu.Root>\n```\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Multi-element support (`button`, `image`) — those are PRODUCT-1507 / PRODUCT-1508\n- Variables dropdown — Resend-specific, stays in dashboard\n- Toast notifications — Resend-specific, stays in dashboard\n- Theme CSS — Layer 2, PRODUCT-1510\n- `ses:no-track` attribute — stays in dashboard's custom Link extension\n",
