            "content": "# Image Bubble Menu Primitives — Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Extract image bubble menu from dashboard into `@react-email/editor` as compound component primitives (Root, Toolbar, EditLink), then migrate dashboard to consume them. ReplaceImage stays in dashboard (Resend-specific).\n\n**Architecture:** Follows the `button-bubble-menu/` compound component pattern exactly — Root (wraps tiptap BubbleMenu + context), Toolbar (conditional visibility), EditLink (action button). The image BM differs from button BM only in `shouldShow` (`isActive('image')` vs `isActive('button')`), data attribute prefix (`data-re-img-bm-*` vs `data-re-btn-bm-*`), and error message text. ReplaceImage is dashboard-only — it uses `startImageUpload` which hits Resend's `/api/upload-image` endpoint and AI alt-text generation.\n\n**Tech Stack:** React, TipTap v3, Vitest + happy-dom, Biome, tsdown\n\n**Linear:** PRODUCT-1507 (OSS primitives), PRODUCT-1513 (dashboard migration)\n\n---\n\n## Conflict avoidance\n\nBranch from `feat/editor-button-bubble-menu-primitives` (the button BM PR branch). This avoids conflicts on `ui/index.ts` and `package.json` since the button BM work is already included. When button BM merges into `feat/ai-oss-editor`, the image BM PR will have a clean diff.\n\n---\n\n## Setup\n\n### Task 0: Worktree setup (react-email repo)\n\n**Step 1: Create worktree from button BM branch**\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/jopcmelo/Developer/resend/react-email\ngit worktree add .worktrees/image-bubble-menu feat/editor-button-bubble-menu-primitives -b feat/editor-image-bubble-menu-primitives\n```\n\n**Step 2: Install deps and verify baseline**\n\n```bash\ncd .worktrees/image-bubble-menu/packages/editor\npnpm install\npnpm test\n```\n\nExpected: 23 passing suites, 203 tests (baseline from button BM branch including onMouseDown fix)\n\n---\n\n## OSS Primitives (react-email repo)\n\nAll work in `.worktrees/image-bubble-menu/packages/editor/src/ui/image-bubble-menu/`.\n\nReference: `button-bubble-menu/` directory for patterns (nearly identical).\n\n### Task 1: Context\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/context.tsx`\n- Test: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/context.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write the test**\n\n```tsx\n// context.spec.tsx\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { useImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\n\ndescribe('useImageBubbleMenuContext', () => {\n  it('throws when used outside a Provider', () => {\n    expect(() => {\n      renderHook(() => useImageBubbleMenuContext());\n    }).toThrow(\n      'ImageBubbleMenu compound components must be used within <ImageBubbleMenu.Root>',\n    );\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/context.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL (module not found)\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```tsx\n// context.tsx\nimport type { Editor } from '@tiptap/core';\nimport * as React from 'react';\n\nexport interface ImageBubbleMenuContextValue {\n  editor: Editor;\n  isEditing: boolean;\n  setIsEditing: (value: boolean) => void;\n}\n\nexport const ImageBubbleMenuContext =\n  React.createContext<ImageBubbleMenuContextValue | null>(null);\n\nexport function useImageBubbleMenuContext(): ImageBubbleMenuContextValue {\n  const context = React.useContext(ImageBubbleMenuContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\n      'ImageBubbleMenu compound components must be used within <ImageBubbleMenu.Root>',\n    );\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\nNote: Same shape as `ButtonBubbleMenuContextValue` — `editor`, `isEditing`, `setIsEditing`. No image-specific state (the dashboard reads image attributes via its own `useEditorState` call).\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/context.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ui/image-bubble-menu/context.tsx src/ui/image-bubble-menu/context.spec.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat: add ImageBubbleMenu context and hook\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Root\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/root.tsx`\n- Test: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write the test**\n\n```tsx\n// root.spec.tsx\nimport { render } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuRoot } from './root';\n\nvi.mock('@tiptap/react', () => ({\n  useCurrentEditor: () => ({ editor: null }),\n  useEditorState: () => null,\n}));\n\nvi.mock('@tiptap/react/menus', () => ({\n  BubbleMenu: ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => (\n    <div data-testid=\"bubble-menu\">{children}</div>\n  ),\n}));\n\ndescribe('ImageBubbleMenuRoot', () => {\n  it('returns null when editor is null', () => {\n    const { container } = render(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuRoot>\n        <span>child</span>\n      </ImageBubbleMenuRoot>,\n    );\n    expect(container.innerHTML).toBe('');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL (module not found)\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```tsx\n// root.tsx\nimport { useCurrentEditor } from '@tiptap/react';\nimport { BubbleMenu } from '@tiptap/react/menus';\nimport * as React from 'react';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\n\nexport interface ImageBubbleMenuRootProps {\n  /** Called when the bubble menu hides */\n  onHide?: () => void;\n  /** Placement relative to cursor (default: 'top') */\n  placement?: 'top' | 'bottom';\n  /** Offset from cursor in px (default: 8) */\n  offset?: number;\n  /** className on the outer wrapper */\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function ImageBubbleMenuRoot({\n  onHide,\n  placement = 'top',\n  offset = 8,\n  className,\n  children,\n}: ImageBubbleMenuRootProps) {\n  const { editor } = useCurrentEditor();\n  const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = React.useState(false);\n\n  if (!editor) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <BubbleMenu\n      editor={editor}\n      data-re-img-bm=\"\"\n      shouldShow={({ editor: e, view }) =>\n        e.isActive('image') && !view.dom.classList.contains('dragging')\n      }\n      options={{\n        placement,\n        offset,\n        onHide: () => {\n          setIsEditing(false);\n          onHide?.();\n        },\n      }}\n      className={className}\n    >\n      <ImageBubbleMenuContext.Provider\n        value={{ editor, isEditing, setIsEditing }}\n      >\n        {children}\n      </ImageBubbleMenuContext.Provider>\n    </BubbleMenu>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nKey differences from `ButtonBubbleMenuRoot`:\n- `shouldShow`: `isActive('image')` instead of `isActive('button')`\n- `data-re-img-bm` instead of `data-re-btn-bm`\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ui/image-bubble-menu/root.tsx src/ui/image-bubble-menu/root.spec.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat: add ImageBubbleMenu.Root compound component\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Toolbar\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/toolbar.tsx`\n- Test: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/toolbar.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write the test**\n\n```tsx\n// toolbar.spec.tsx\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport type { ReactNode } from 'react';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuToolbar } from './toolbar';\n\nconst mockEditor = {} as any;\n\nfunction renderWithContext(\n  ui: ReactNode,\n  { isEditing = false }: { isEditing?: boolean } = {},\n) {\n  return render(\n    <ImageBubbleMenuContext.Provider\n      value={{\n        editor: mockEditor,\n        isEditing,\n        setIsEditing: vi.fn(),\n      }}\n    >\n      {ui}\n    </ImageBubbleMenuContext.Provider>,\n  );\n}\n\ndescribe('ImageBubbleMenuToolbar', () => {\n  it('renders children when not editing', () => {\n    renderWithContext(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuToolbar>\n        <button type=\"button\">Edit</button>\n      </ImageBubbleMenuToolbar>,\n      { isEditing: false },\n    );\n    expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Edit' })).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('renders null when editing', () => {\n    const { container } = renderWithContext(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuToolbar>\n        <button type=\"button\">Edit</button>\n      </ImageBubbleMenuToolbar>,\n      { isEditing: true },\n    );\n    expect(container.querySelector('[data-re-img-bm-toolbar]')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('applies className', () => {\n    const { container } = renderWithContext(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuToolbar className=\"custom\">\n        <span>child</span>\n      </ImageBubbleMenuToolbar>,\n    );\n    expect(container.querySelector('[data-re-img-bm-toolbar]')?.className).toBe(\n      'custom',\n    );\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/toolbar.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```tsx\n// toolbar.tsx\nimport type * as React from 'react';\nimport { useImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\n\nexport interface ImageBubbleMenuToolbarProps {\n  className?: string;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function ImageBubbleMenuToolbar({\n  className,\n  children,\n}: ImageBubbleMenuToolbarProps) {\n  const { isEditing } = useImageBubbleMenuContext();\n\n  if (isEditing) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div data-re-img-bm-toolbar=\"\" className={className}>\n      {children}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/toolbar.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ui/image-bubble-menu/toolbar.tsx src/ui/image-bubble-menu/toolbar.spec.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat: add ImageBubbleMenu.Toolbar compound component\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: EditLink\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/edit-link.tsx`\n- Test: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/edit-link.spec.tsx`\n\n**Step 1: Write the test**\n\n```tsx\n// edit-link.spec.tsx\nimport { fireEvent, render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport type { ReactNode } from 'react';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuEditLink } from './edit-link';\n\nconst mockSetIsEditing = vi.fn();\n\nfunction renderWithContext(ui: ReactNode) {\n  return render(\n    <ImageBubbleMenuContext.Provider\n      value={{\n        editor: {} as any,\n        isEditing: false,\n        setIsEditing: mockSetIsEditing,\n      }}\n    >\n      {ui}\n    </ImageBubbleMenuContext.Provider>,\n  );\n}\n\ndescribe('ImageBubbleMenuEditLink', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    mockSetIsEditing.mockClear();\n  });\n\n  it('renders a button with edit link aria-label', () => {\n    renderWithContext(<ImageBubbleMenuEditLink />);\n    expect(screen.getByLabelText('Edit link')).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('calls setIsEditing(true) on click', () => {\n    renderWithContext(<ImageBubbleMenuEditLink />);\n    fireEvent.click(screen.getByLabelText('Edit link'));\n    expect(mockSetIsEditing).toHaveBeenCalledWith(true);\n  });\n\n  it('prevents default on mousedown to avoid editor blur', () => {\n    renderWithContext(<ImageBubbleMenuEditLink />);\n    const button = screen.getByLabelText('Edit link');\n    const event = new MouseEvent('mousedown', { bubbles: true });\n    const preventSpy = vi.spyOn(event, 'preventDefault');\n    button.dispatchEvent(event);\n    expect(preventSpy).toHaveBeenCalled();\n  });\n\n  it('composes user onMouseDown while still preventing default', () => {\n    const userOnMouseDown = vi.fn();\n    renderWithContext(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuEditLink onMouseDown={userOnMouseDown} />,\n    );\n    const button = screen.getByLabelText('Edit link');\n    const event = new MouseEvent('mousedown', { bubbles: true });\n    const preventSpy = vi.spyOn(event, 'preventDefault');\n    button.dispatchEvent(event);\n    expect(preventSpy).toHaveBeenCalled();\n    expect(userOnMouseDown).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);\n  });\n\n  it('renders custom children instead of default icon', () => {\n    renderWithContext(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuEditLink>\n        <span>Custom</span>\n      </ImageBubbleMenuEditLink>,\n    );\n    expect(screen.getByText('Custom')).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  it('applies className', () => {\n    const { container } = renderWithContext(\n      <ImageBubbleMenuEditLink className=\"my-class\" />,\n    );\n    expect(container.querySelector('[data-item=\"edit-link\"]')?.className).toBe(\n      'my-class',\n    );\n  });\n\n  it('has correct data attributes', () => {\n    const { container } = renderWithContext(<ImageBubbleMenuEditLink />);\n    const button = container.querySelector('[data-re-img-bm-item]');\n    expect(button).toBeDefined();\n    expect(button?.getAttribute('data-item')).toBe('edit-link');\n  });\n\n  it('composes user onClick with setIsEditing', () => {\n    const userOnClick = vi.fn();\n    renderWithContext(<ImageBubbleMenuEditLink onClick={userOnClick} />);\n    fireEvent.click(screen.getByLabelText('Edit link'));\n    expect(userOnClick).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);\n    expect(mockSetIsEditing).toHaveBeenCalledWith(true);\n  });\n\n  it('spreads rest props onto button', () => {\n    renderWithContext(<ImageBubbleMenuEditLink data-testid=\"custom\" />);\n    expect(screen.getByTestId('custom')).toBeDefined();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/edit-link.spec.tsx`\nExpected: FAIL\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```tsx\n// edit-link.tsx\nimport { LinkIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport type * as React from 'react';\nimport { useImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\n\nexport interface ImageBubbleMenuEditLinkProps\n  extends Omit<React.ComponentProps<'button'>, 'type'> {}\n\nexport function ImageBubbleMenuEditLink({\n  className,\n  children,\n  onClick,\n  onMouseDown,\n  ...rest\n}: ImageBubbleMenuEditLinkProps) {\n  const { setIsEditing } = useImageBubbleMenuContext();\n\n  return (\n    <button\n      {...rest}\n      type=\"button\"\n      aria-label=\"Edit link\"\n      data-re-img-bm-item=\"\"\n      data-item=\"edit-link\"\n      className={className}\n      onMouseDown={(e) => {\n        e.preventDefault();\n        onMouseDown?.(e);\n      }}\n      onClick={(e) => {\n        onClick?.(e);\n        setIsEditing(true);\n      }}\n    >\n      {children ?? <LinkIcon />}\n    </button>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nSame as `ButtonBubbleMenuEditLink` except `data-re-img-bm-item` prefix.\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `pnpm test -- --reporter=verbose src/ui/image-bubble-menu/edit-link.spec.tsx`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ui/image-bubble-menu/edit-link.tsx src/ui/image-bubble-menu/edit-link.spec.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat: add ImageBubbleMenu.EditLink compound component\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: CSS, barrel exports, version bump\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/image-bubble-menu.css`\n- Create: `src/ui/image-bubble-menu/index.ts`\n- Modify: `src/ui/index.ts` — add `export * from './image-bubble-menu'`\n- Modify: `package.json` — bump to `0.0.0-experimental.12`\n\n**Step 1: Create CSS**\n\n```css\n/* image-bubble-menu.css */\n/* Minimal functional styles for ImageBubbleMenu compound components.\n * Layout and positioning only - no visual design.\n * Import optionally: import '@react-email/editor/styles/image-bubble-menu.css';\n */\n\n[data-re-img-bm] {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n}\n\n[data-re-img-bm-toolbar] {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n}\n\n[data-re-img-bm-item] {\n  display: inline-flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  border: none;\n  background: none;\n  padding: 0.5rem;\n}\n\n[data-re-img-bm-item] svg {\n  width: 1rem;\n  height: 1rem;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create barrel exports**\n\n```ts\n// index.ts\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuEditLink } from './edit-link';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuRoot } from './root';\nimport { ImageBubbleMenuToolbar } from './toolbar';\n\nexport { useImageBubbleMenuContext } from './context';\nexport type { ImageBubbleMenuEditLinkProps } from './edit-link';\nexport { ImageBubbleMenuEditLink } from './edit-link';\nexport type { ImageBubbleMenuRootProps } from './root';\nexport { ImageBubbleMenuRoot } from './root';\nexport type { ImageBubbleMenuToolbarProps } from './toolbar';\nexport { ImageBubbleMenuToolbar } from './toolbar';\n\nexport const ImageBubbleMenu = {\n  Root: ImageBubbleMenuRoot,\n  Toolbar: ImageBubbleMenuToolbar,\n  EditLink: ImageBubbleMenuEditLink,\n} as const;\n```\n\n**Step 3: Add to top-level UI exports**\n\nIn `src/ui/index.ts`, add between button-bubble-menu and link-bubble-menu (alphabetical):\n\n```ts\nexport * from './bubble-menu';\nexport * from './button-bubble-menu';\nexport * from './image-bubble-menu';\nexport * from './link-bubble-menu';\n```\n\n**Step 4: Bump version**\n\nIn `package.json`, change `\"version\"` from `\"0.0.0-experimental.11\"` to `\"0.0.0-experimental.12\"`.\n\n**Step 5: Run full test suite, lint, build**\n\n```bash\npnpm test\nnpx biome check src/ui/image-bubble-menu/\npnpm build\n```\n\nExpected: all tests pass, lint clean, build green (CSS copied by `scripts/copy-css.mjs`)\n\n**Step 6: Verify exports in built types**\n\n```bash\nrg 'ImageBubbleMenu' dist/index.d.mts\n```\n\nExpected: `ImageBubbleMenu`, `ImageBubbleMenuRoot`, `ImageBubbleMenuEditLink`, `ImageBubbleMenuToolbar`, `useImageBubbleMenuContext` all present.\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ui/image-bubble-menu/image-bubble-menu.css src/ui/image-bubble-menu/index.ts src/ui/index.ts package.json\ngit commit -m \"feat: add ImageBubbleMenu barrel exports, CSS, bump to experimental.12\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Push and open PR\n\n**Step 1: Push branch**\n\n```bash\ngit push -u origin feat/editor-image-bubble-menu-primitives\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create PR**\n\n```bash\ngh pr create --base feat/ai-oss-editor \\\n  --title \"feat: ImageBubbleMenu compound component primitives\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- New `ImageBubbleMenu` compound primitives: `Root`, `Toolbar`, `EditLink`\n- Context: `useImageBubbleMenuContext` hook for consumer state sync\n- Minimal layout CSS with `data-re-img-bm-*` attribute selectors\n- Bump to `0.0.0-experimental.12`\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `Root` | Wraps tiptap BubbleMenu, shouldShow on `image` node + dragging guard, manages isEditing state |\n| `Toolbar` | Conditional wrapper, hides when isEditing |\n| `EditLink` | Button to enter edit mode, default LinkIcon, composed onClick/onMouseDown |\n\n## Design decision\n\n`ReplaceImage` is intentionally NOT included as an OSS primitive — it depends on Resend's upload infrastructure and AI alt-text generation. The dashboard renders its own ReplaceImage button inside `<ImageBubbleMenu.Toolbar>` as a regular `<button>`.\n\n## Linear\n\nPRODUCT-1507\nEOF\n)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dashboard Migration (dashboard repo)\n\n### Task 7: Install and rewrite\n\n**Step 1: Create branch from main**\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/jopcmelo/Developer/resend/dashboard\ngit checkout main && git pull\ngit checkout -b feat/editor-image-bubble-menu-oss\n```\n\n**Step 2: Install new editor version**\n\nPack tarball from react-email worktree, clear cache, install:\n\n```bash\n# In react-email worktree\ncd /Users/jopcmelo/Developer/resend/react-email/.worktrees/image-bubble-menu/packages/editor\npnpm pack\n\n# In dashboard\ncd /Users/jopcmelo/Developer/resend/dashboard\nrm -rf node_modules/@react-email/editor\npnpm add \"<path-to-tarball>\"\n```\n\nVerify: `rg 'ImageBubbleMenu' node_modules/@react-email/editor/dist/index.d.mts`\n\n**Step 3: Rewrite bubble-menu-image.tsx**\n\nReplace the full file with:\n\n```tsx\nimport { NodeSelection } from '@tiptap/pm/state';\nimport { useEditorState } from '@tiptap/react';\nimport {\n  ImageBubbleMenu,\n  useImageBubbleMenuContext,\n} from '@react-email/editor';\nimport { RefreshCwIcon } from 'lucide-react';\nimport * as React from 'react';\nimport { cn } from '@/lib/cn';\nimport { startImageUpload } from '../../extensions/upload-image';\nimport { LinkSelector } from './link-selector';\n\nconst ITEM_CLASSNAME = cn(\n  'p-2 text-gray-10 hover:bg-gray-a2 active:bg-gray-a3 dark:hover:bg-gray-a3 dark:active:bg-gray-a4',\n  '[&_svg]:h-4 [&_svg]:w-4',\n);\n\nexport function EditorBubbleMenuImage() {\n  const [isLinkSelectorOpen, setIsLinkSelectorOpen] = React.useState(false);\n\n  return (\n    <ImageBubbleMenu.Root\n      onHide={() => {\n        setIsLinkSelectorOpen(false);\n      }}\n      className=\"flex h-[38px] w-[200px] items-center justify-center\"\n    >\n      <ImageBubbleMenuContent\n        isLinkSelectorOpen={isLinkSelectorOpen}\n        setIsLinkSelectorOpen={setIsLinkSelectorOpen}\n      />\n    </ImageBubbleMenu.Root>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction ImageBubbleMenuContent({\n  isLinkSelectorOpen,\n  setIsLinkSelectorOpen,\n}: {\n  isLinkSelectorOpen: boolean;\n  setIsLinkSelectorOpen: (state: boolean) => void;\n}) {\n  const { editor, setIsEditing } = useImageBubbleMenuContext();\n\n  const editorState = useEditorState({\n    editor,\n    selector: ({ editor: e }) => {\n      const { selection } = e.state;\n      if (\n        !(selection instanceof NodeSelection) ||\n        selection.node.type.name !== 'image'\n      ) {\n        return {\n          isImageSelected: false,\n          imagePos: null,\n          alignment: 'left',\n          href: '',\n          width: '100%',\n          height: 'auto',\n        };\n      }\n\n      const attrs = selection.node.attrs as Record<string, unknown>;\n      const alignment =\n        (attrs.align as string | undefined) ||\n        (attrs.alignment as string | undefined) ||\n        'left';\n      const href = (attrs.href as string | undefined) || '';\n      const width = attrs.width ?? '100%';\n      const height = attrs.height ?? 'auto';\n\n      return {\n        isImageSelected: true,\n        imagePos: selection.from,\n        alignment,\n        href,\n        width,\n        height,\n      };\n    },\n  });\n\n  const replaceImage = () => {\n    if (!editorState?.isImageSelected) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const widthValue = String(editorState.width);\n    const heightValue = String(editorState.height);\n\n    const input = document.createElement('input');\n    input.type = 'file';\n    input.accept = 'image/*';\n    input.onchange = async () => {\n      if (input.files?.length) {\n        const file = input.files[0];\n        const pos = editorState.imagePos ?? editor.view.state.selection.from;\n\n        await startImageUpload(\n          file,\n          editor.view,\n          pos,\n          {\n            width: widthValue,\n            height: heightValue,\n            alignment: editorState.alignment,\n            href: editorState.href,\n          },\n          editor.storage.metadata,\n        );\n      }\n    };\n    input.click();\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      <ImageBubbleMenu.Toolbar>\n        <div className=\"bg-background overflow-hidden flex divide-x divide-gray-3 rounded-xl border border-gray-3 shadow-xl dark:divide-gray-3\">\n          <button\n            type=\"button\"\n            aria-label=\"Replace image\"\n            className={ITEM_CLASSNAME}\n            onMouseDown={(e) => e.preventDefault()}\n            onClick={replaceImage}\n          >\n            <RefreshCwIcon />\n          </button>\n          <ImageBubbleMenu.EditLink\n            className={ITEM_CLASSNAME}\n            onClick={() => setIsLinkSelectorOpen(true)}\n          />\n        </div>\n      </Ima