          "text": "We need postcss (specifically `postcss-import`) to flatten `@import` statements in `default.css` at build time.\n\nThe theme file uses `@import` to pull in the 4 Layer 0 layout CSS files:\n\n```css\n@import '../bubble-menu/bubble-menu.css';\n@import '../link-bubble-menu/link-bubble-menu.css';\n@import '../button-bubble-menu/button-bubble-menu.css';\n@import '../image-bubble-menu/image-bubble-menu.css';\n```\n\n**Why not ship `@import` as-is?** No popular library does this. Consumer bundlers handle `@import` from `node_modules` inconsistently — some resolve them, some don't. Radix Themes uses the same pattern: `@import` in source, postcss-import flattens to a single file at build, ships zero `@import` in the published package.\n\nSo the consumer just does `import '@react-email/editor/themes/default.css'` and gets one flat file with both layout + visual styles. No chained imports to resolve.",
