            "command": "gh pr edit 3029 --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- Add optional default theme CSS: `import '@react-email/editor/themes/default.css'`\n- CSS custom properties with light defaults and dark mode (`prefers-color-scheme` + `.dark` class)\n- Covers all 4 bubble menus: text, link, button, image\n- Layer 0 layout CSS inlined via postcss-import at build time (Radix Themes pattern)\n- Fix missing CSS exports for `button-bubble-menu.css` and `image-bubble-menu.css`\n- Fix cross-platform path detection in CSS build script\n- Pin non-tiptap dependency versions, keep `^3.17.1` ranges for tiptap (consumer compatibility)\n- Bump to `0.0.0-experimental.13`\n\n## How it works\n\nThe theme file ships as a single flat CSS file (no `@import` in the published output). At build time, `postcss-import` inlines the Layer 0 layout CSS into the theme, so consumers only need one import:\n\n```js\nimport '@react-email/editor/themes/default.css';\n```\n\nThis gives them both layout (flexbox, resets, sizing) and visual styling (colors, borders, shadows, hover states, dark mode) for all bubble menu primitives.\n\n## Customization\n\nConsumers have two levels of customization:\n\n### 1. CSS variables — theme-wide control\n\nOverride any `--re-*` variable on a parent element to change the look across all bubble menus at once:\n\n```css\n.my-editor {\n  --re-bg: #1a1a1a;\n  --re-border: #333;\n  --re-text: #f0f0f0;\n  --re-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);\n}\n```\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Light default |\n|----------|---------|---------------|\n| `--re-bg` | Background | `#fff` |\n| `--re-border` | Borders and dividers | `#e5e5e5` |\n| `--re-text` | Primary text/icon color | `#1c1c1c` |\n| `--re-text-muted` | Secondary text color | `#6b6b6b` |\n| `--re-hover` | Hover background | `rgba(0,0,0,0.04)` |\n| `--re-active` | Active/click background | `rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` |\n| `--re-pressed` | Pressed/toggled background | `rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` |\n| `--re-separator` | Separator color | `#e5e5e5` |\n| `--re-radius` | Border radius (containers) | `0.75rem` |\n| `--re-radius-sm` | Border radius (items) | `0.5rem` |\n| `--re-shadow` | Box shadow | Tailwind `shadow-xl` equivalent |\n| `--re-danger` | Danger/unlink color | `#dc2626` |\n| `--re-danger-hover` | Danger hover background | `rgba(220,38,38,0.1)` |\n\nDark mode is included out of the box via `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` and a `.dark` class selector.\n\n### 2. Data attributes — per-component control\n\nEvery primitive renders a `data-re-*` attribute. Consumers can target any specific component directly in CSS for surgical overrides:\n\n```css\n/* Make only the node selector dropdown wider */\n[data-re-node-selector-content] {\n  min-width: 14rem;\n}\n\n/* Custom hover color for link bubble menu items only */\n[data-re-link-bm-item]:hover {\n  background: #e0f2fe;\n}\n\n/* Different shadow for the text formatting menu */\n[data-re-bubble-menu] {\n  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);\n}\n```\n\nBoth approaches work together — use variables for broad theme changes, data attributes for targeted overrides.\n\n## Individual Layer 0 CSS imports (advanced)\n\nConsumers who want layout-only CSS without any visual styling (to build their own theme from scratch) can import the per-menu layout files directly:\n\n```js\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/bubble-menu.css';\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/link-bubble-menu.css';\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/button-bubble-menu.css';\nimport '@react-email/editor/styles/image-bubble-menu.css';\n```\n\nThese provide only structural CSS (flexbox, resets, icon sizing) with zero colors, borders, or shadows.\n\n## Linear\n\nPRODUCT-1509, PRODUCT-1510\nEOF\n)\"",
