me for formatting\n- **All bubble menus should default to `placement=\"top\"`** — consistency decision made during this conversation.\n- **Use git worktrees** for isolated development. Dashboard uses `.worktrees/`. React-email has `.worktrees/` in `.gitignore`.\n- **Implementation plans** are saved to `/Users/jopcmelo/.local/share/opencode/plans/`\n- **Tiptap deps must use `^3.17.1` ranges** (not pinned) because dashboard uses 3.17.1 and pinning to 3.20.0 causes duplicate tiptap singletons at runtime\n- **CSS distribution**: No `@import` in published CSS files. Use `postcss` + `postcss-import` to flatten at build time (Radix Themes pattern). Consumers get a single flat file.\n- **Theme CSS approach**: CSS custom properties (`--re-*`) with sensible light defaults + dark mode via both `prefers-color-scheme` and `.dark` class. Two customization levels: variables for broad theme changes, `data-re-*` attributes for per-component surgical overrides.\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **Editor V2 architecture** lives at `dashboard/src/components/editor-v2/` with layers: `core/ → extensions/ → plugins/ → ui/`. Uses TipTap v3, `@react-email/editor` for EmailNode extensions, Liveblocks for collaboration, custom `EditorEventBus` for cross-component communication.\n\n2. **Dashboard already depends on `@react-email/editor`** — version `0.0.0-experimental.12` is published to npm. Theme CSS PR bumps to `.13`.\n\n3. **Module augmentation doesn't work in bundled .d.ts** — The original `types.ts` used `declare module '../../core/event-bus'` to augment `EditorEventMap`, but after bundling into a single `.d.ts`, the relative path becomes meaningless. Fix: declare events shipped with the package directly in the base `EditorEventMap` interface in `event-bus.ts`.\n\n4. **NodeSelector compound API** — Refactored from monolithic to Radix-style compound sub-components: `NodeSelector.Root`, `NodeSelector.Trigger`, `NodeSelector.Content`.\n\n5. **Tarball install gotcha** — pnpm caches tarballs aggressive